1. 用handle_testing_data_sentence.py把测试数据处理
2. 用labeling里的main_benchmarks 做标注  weiyang   得到 test_wy.p
3. 用labeling_by_bert_20200108里的main_benchmarks 做标注 得到  test_bert.p
4. 处理要用于seq2graph的模型的数据  process_for_seq2graph.py
5. test_seq2graph.py
## Dev Inference from New .story Files

This is the end-to-end flow for running dev inference on new `.story` files.

### 1) Build `dev_full.p` from `.story`

```
python handle_testing_data.py \
  --input_dir testing_data_hmt_20201012_final/dev_full_original_new/ \
  --output processed/dev_full_new.p
```

### 2) Build seq2graph input (with labels)

```
python process_for_seq2graph.py \
  --input processed/dev_full_new.p \
  --output_dir processed_for_seq2graph_dev_new/ \
  --labels to_dev/dev_bert.p

If you don't have labels, you can generate them on the fly:

```
python process_for_seq2graph.py \
  --input processed/dev_full_new.p \
  --output_dir processed_for_seq2graph_dev_new/ \
  --label_mode distilbert \
  --device cpu
```

If you want to use gold labels from `a_labeling_dev`:

```
python process_for_seq2graph.py \
  --input processed/dev_full_new.p \
  --output_dir processed_for_seq2graph_dev_new/ \
  --label_mode gold \
  --gold_dir testing_data_hmt_20201012_final/a_labeling_dev
```
```

This writes:

```
processed_for_seq2graph_dev_new/dev_for_mymodel_info.p
processed_for_seq2graph_dev_new/max_info.p
```

### 3) (Optional) Build coreference maps for dev

If you use GCN coreference maps, generate them for the new dev pickle:

```
python ../create_coreference_maps.py \
  --input processed/dev_full_new.p \
  --output_dir ../directed_maps_simple
```

This creates `directed_maps_simple/DGLgraph/dev_full_new.p` if DGL is available.

### 4) Run inference

```
python test_seq2graph.py \
  --coref_test_maps ../directed_maps_simple/DGLgraph/dev_full_new.p
```
